== Partition sequences and Pochhammer products ==

=== Regular partition number sequence ===

The regular partition sequence formula_174 itself indicates the number of ways in which a positive integer number formula_175 can be splitted into positive integer summands. For the numbers formula_176 to formula_177, the associated partition numbers formula_178 with all associated number partitions are listed in the following table:

The generating function of the regular partition number sequence can be represented via Pochhammer product in the following way:
: formula_179

The summandization of the now mentioned Pochhammer product is described by the Pentagonal number theorem in this way:

:formula_180

The following basic definitions apply to the pentagonal numbers and the card house numbers:

: formula_181
: formula_182

As a further application one obtains a formula for the third power of the Euler product:
:formula_183

=== Strict partition number sequence ===

And the strict partition sequence formula_184 indicates the number of ways in which such a positive integer number formula_175 can be splitted into positive integer summands such that each summand appears at most once and no summand value occurs repeatedly. Exactly the same sequence is also generated if in the partition only odd summands are included, but these odd summands may occur more than once. Both representations for the strict partition number sequence are compared in the following table:

The generating function of the strict partition number sequence can be represented using Pochhammer&#x27;s product:
: formula_186

=== Overpartition number sequence ===

The Maclaurin series for the reciprocal of the function has the numbers of over partition sequence as coefficients with a positive sign:

: formula_187
: formula_188

If, for a given number formula_189, all partitions are set up in such a way that the summand size never increases, and all those summands that do not have a summand of the same size to the left of themselves can be marked for each partition of this type, then it will be the resulting number of the marked partitions depending on formula_189 by the overpartition function formula_191 .

First example:

: formula_192

These 14 possibilities of partition markings exist for the sum 4:

Second example:

: formula_193

These 24 possibilities of partition markings exist for the sum 5:

