<doc id="449763" wikidata="Q35250" url="?curid=449763" title="Kajuk language">
<text>The Kajuk language, Ekajuk (also spelled &quot;Akajo&quot; and &quot;Akajuk&quot;), is an Ekoid language (of the Niger–Congo family) spoken in the Cross River State and some surrounding regions of Nigeria.

The Ekajuk are one of several peoples who use the nsibidi ideographs.

